Question:                                                                            (22-07-2021)
----------
ReverseAndNot

Write a function that takes an integer i and returns a string with the integer backwards followed by the original integer.



To illustrate:



"123"

We reverse "123" to get "321" and then add "123" to the end, resulting in "321123".



Examples

reverseAndNot(123) ? "321123"



reverseAndNot(152) ? "251152"



reverseAndNot(123456789) ? "987654321123456789"

Notes

i is a non-negative integer.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Solution:
----------
#include<iostream>

#include<cstring>

#include<algorithm>

using namespace std;



int main(){

	int a=123456;

	string b=to_string(a);         //a is converted to string and stored in b and c

	string c=to_string(a);

	reverse(c.begin(),c.end());    //c is reversed   //reverse function is in algorithm library

	string d=c+b;                  //strings can be added like this

	cout<<d;

}
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Learnings:
------------
1.Reverse function in algorithm library

2.to_string function in string library 
